      "end": 10.68,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, visit LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 11.94,
      "end": 17.1,
      "text": "This is a recording by Kristin Luoma, green k-r-i.com.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 19.16,
      "end": 20.42,
      "text": "Asop's fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 22.6,
      "end": 23.92,
      "text": "The wolf in sheep's clothing.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 26.84,
      "end": 33.06,
      "text": "A wolf resolved to disguise himself in order that he might pray upon a flock of sheep without fear of detection.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 34.16,
      "end": 38.84,
      "text": "So he clothed himself in a sheepskin, and slipped among the sheep when they were out at pasture.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 40.16,
      "end": 45.58,
      "text": "He completely deceived the shepherd, and when the flock was pended for the night, he was shut in with the rest.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 46.88,
      "end": 53.9,
      "text": "But that very night, as it happened, the shepherd, requiring a supply of mutton for the table, laid hands on the wolf's feet.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 53.9,
      "end": 57.58,
      "text": "He was a wolf in mistake for a sheep, and killed him with his knife on the spot.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 59.88,
      "end": 62.0,
      "text": "End of the wolf in sheep's clothing.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
